BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:294@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260508
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260509
SUMMARY:BWA: Deadline -  International Families Day Participation Form
DESCRIPTION:Deadline to complete the online form for parent volunteers and food donations for International Families Day.\n\nParents and carers must complete the online Google Form by today if they wish to volunteer to visit school and share their culture (skills, stories, or activities) or if they intend to donate food or money for the international buffet. The form is used to coordinate volunteers and manage dietary requirements for the event on May 15th.
CATEGORIES:ADMIN
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:295@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260511
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260512
SUMMARY:BWA: Deadline -  International Families Day Homework Project
DESCRIPTION:Pupils should submit their creative projects celebrating their heritage to their class teacher.\n\nAll pupils are invited to complete a project of their choice celebrating their heritage. Ideas include family trees, sculptures of landmarks, show and tell preparations, books, or poems. Projects should be handed in to class teachers today. Some pupils will share these projects in an assembly during this week.
CATEGORIES:ACADEMIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:296@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260515
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260516
SUMMARY:BWA: International Families Day -  Dress Up
DESCRIPTION:Pupils are invited to dress in national clothing or flag colours to celebrate the school's international community.\n\nTo celebrate International Families Day, pupils should come dressed in national dress or the colours of the flag that represents their country or heritage. Note: If your child has a PE lesson on this day, please ensure the outfit is suitable for physical activity.
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:297@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260515
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260516
SUMMARY:BWA: International Families Day -  Buffet
DESCRIPTION:An after-school international buffet for all families in the lower hall, canteen, and playground.\n\nFamilies are invited to join an international buffet starting at 3:30pm in the lower hall. Food can be enjoyed in the canteen and playground. \n\nFood Donations: Donated dishes should be brought to the school office from 2:30pm today. All food MUST be nut-free and labeled with the provided ingredient slip (specifying if it is spicy, vegetarian, vegan, or halal).
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
